## 12. Gamification Patterns (Duolingo-inspired)

- **Streak counter**: flame icon (`--color-streak`), bold number, top of profile/header
- **XP counter**: lightning bolt icon (`--color-xp`), shown in nav or profile
- **League badge**: shield icon with tier color (`bronze`, `silver`, `gold`)
- **Progress circles**: circular SVG progress rings, stroke = `--color-primary`
- **Achievement cards**: icon + title + description, subtle border, hover lift
- **Leaderboard row**: rank number (bold, muted) + avatar + name + XP value right-aligned

---

## 13. Accessibility

- Minimum contrast ratio: **4.5:1** for body text, **3:1** for large text and UI components
- All interactive elements: visible `:focus-visible` ring (`outline: 2px solid --color-primary; outline-offset: 2px`)
- Icon-only buttons: must have `aria-label`
- Images: always include `alt` text
- Color must never be the sole means of conveying information (pair with icon or text)
- Touch targets: minimum `44×44px`

---

## 14. Component Naming Conventions (for code)

```
CourseCard          — browsable/catalog card
EnrolledCourseCard  — card with progress bar (dashboard)
LessonItem          — single row in course player sidebar
SectionAccordion    — collapsible section in course player
StatBadge           — XP / streak / achievement badge
ProgressBar         — thin horizontal fill bar
CategoryTag         — colored pill label
HeroBanner          — full-width dark/image hero
SectionHeading      — title + subtitle block
NavBar              — top navigation
CourseThumbnail     — 16:9 image with badge overlay
```

---

## 15. Do's and Don'ts

**Do:**
- Use bold, saturated category colors for course card backgrounds (like Image 4)
- Always show lesson/progress metadata on enrolled cards
- Use dark overlays on video thumbnails for text legibility
- Apply consistent 8px grid spacing
- Use pill shapes for tags and search bars
- Animate card hover with subtle lift

**Don't:**
- Don't use more than 2 accent colors in a single card
- Don't use plain gray backgrounds for course cards — color encodes category
- Don't show progress bars on catalog (un-enrolled) cards
- Don't use more than 3 font weights on a single page
- Don't make CTA buttons smaller than 36px height
- Don't skip hover/focus states on any interactive element
- Don't use Inter or Roboto as the primary display font — choose something with more character
